{
  "_comment": [
    "SHARED cross-language parity corpus for CiteVyn name recognition (#84 item 4).",
    "Read by BOTH frontend/src/lib/citevynAliases.test.ts (against mentionsCitevyn)",
    "and backend/tests/test_guardrails_domain.py (against _CITEVYN_RE). Pinning the",
    "alias LIST only proves the two lists agree; it says nothing about the matchers",
    "around them, and the two are written in different regex dialects. This corpus",
    "is the behavioural pin: every case must produce `match` on both sides, so a",
    "structural rewrite on either side that changes an answer fails on the other.",
    "Add a case here, not to one suite, whenever either matcher changes."
